# Formatting Standards

## Indentation

- **4 spaces**, never tabs
- Continuation lines: +4 spaces from start

## Control Flow

`THEN` stays on same line as `IF`/`ELSIF`. `DO` stays on same line as `FOR`/`WHILE`:

```iecst
IF bEnable THEN
    nValue := 1;
ELSIF bFallback THEN
    nValue := 2;
ELSE
    nValue := 0;
END_IF

FOR nIdx := 1 TO 3 DO
    arrValues[nIdx] := 0;
END_FOR
```

**No single-line IF ever** ‚Äî body always on next line:

```iecst
// ‚úÖ
IF bError THEN
    RETURN;
END_IF

// ‚ùå Never
IF bError THEN RETURN; END_IF
```

## CASE Statement

```iecst
CASE nState OF
    0: nValue := 0;
    1: nValue := 1;
       bDone  := TRUE;
    2: A_HandleError();
ELSE
    nValue := -1;
END_CASE
```

Cases indented 4 spaces. Multi-line case body aligned under first statement. `ELSE` at column 0.

## STRUCT / TYPE

STRUCT always on its own line after `:`, not indented:

```iecst
TYPE ST_EMS_Example :
STRUCT
    fCurrent : REAL := 0.0;  // [A] Phase current
    bEnable  : BOOL;         // Enable flag
END_STRUCT
END_TYPE
```

Members indented 4 spaces inside STRUCT. `END_STRUCT` and `END_TYPE` at column 0.

## Declarations ‚Äî Column Alignment

Align `:`, `:=`, and `//` in columns within each VAR block:

```iecst
VAR_INPUT
    bEnable       : BOOL;
    fSetpoint     : REAL := 0.0;
    tTimeout      : TIME := T#5S;
    stMeasurement : ST_EMS_Grid_Measurement;
END_VAR
VAR
    _nStep        : INT;
    _bInitialized : BOOL;
    _fbTonDelay   : TON;
END_VAR
```

## VAR Block Order

1. `VAR_INPUT` ‚Äî inputs
2. `VAR_OUTPUT` ‚Äî outputs
3. `VAR_IN_OUT` ‚Äî references
4. `VAR` ‚Äî private state (group with `(* comment *)` sections)
5. `VAR CONSTANT` ‚Äî constants

Group internal VARs logically:

```iecst
VAR
    (* edge triggers *)
    _posEdgePlugged : R_TRIG;
    _negEdgeDone    : F_TRIG;

    (* timers *)
    _fbTonTest      : TON;
    _fbTonFailsafe  : TON;

    (* state *)
    _nStep          : INT;
    _bActive        : BOOL;
END_VAR
```

## Function Calls

**‚â§4 params** ‚Üí single line. **>4 params** ‚Üí multiline with aligned `:=` / `=>`:

```iecst
fbTimer(IN := TRUE, PT := T#5S, Q =>);        // 3 params: single line OK
fbRead(sIP := sIPAddr, nPort := 502, nUnit := 1, bExec := TRUE); // 4 params: still OK

fbPid(
    bEnable       := TRUE,
    rW            := fSetpoint,
    rX            := fActual,
    rKp           := _stParam.fKp,
    tTi           := _stParam.tTi,
    rY            => _fOutput);          // closing ); on last param line
```

## Array / Enum Initializers

- **Array:** ‚â§30 elements on one line, >30 ‚Üí multiline
- **Enum:** ‚â§5 members on one line, >5 ‚Üí multiline (one per line)

```iecst
// 5 enum members ‚Äî single line OK
TYPE E_Mode : ( IDLE := 0, AUTO := 1, MANUAL := 2, ERROR := 99 ) := IDLE; END_TYPE

// >5 ‚Äî multiline
TYPE E_State :
(
    IDLE      := 0,
    STARTING  := 1,
    RUNNING   := 2,
    STOPPING  := 3,
    ERROR     := 99
) := IDLE;
END_TYPE
```

## Long Line Wrapping

Wrap at **200 characters**. Wrap **after** binary operators (not before):

```iecst
// ‚úÖ Wrap after operator
nResult := nValue1 + nValue2 +
           nValue3 + nValue4;

// ‚ùå Wrong ‚Äî wrap before operator
nResult := nValue1
           + nValue2 + nValue3;
```

## Assignment Alignment

Align `:=` in related assignment groups:

```iecst
_fMaxPower_L1 := 0;
_fMaxPower_L2 := 0;
_fMaxPower_L3 := 0;
_bStartTest   := TRUE;
_bCheckDone   := FALSE;
```

## Blank Lines

- **1 blank line** before/after `IF`/`CASE`/`FOR`/`WHILE` blocks
- **0 blank lines** between `END_VAR` and first statement
- **1 blank line** between logical groups inside a block
- **Max 1** consecutive blank line

## Spaces

- Around operators: `:=`, `+`, `-`, `*`, `/`, `=`, `<>`, `AND`, `OR`
- After commas: `CONCAT(s1, s2)`
- Around `:` in declarations: `nValue : INT`
- **No** space before `.` / `[` / `(`
- **No** space after `(` or before `)`

## Comments

See `twincat3-comments.mdc` for full rules. Summary:
- VAR_INPUT / VAR_OUTPUT: every variable gets `// [unit] Purpose`
- VAR sections: group with `(* section name *)`
- Code blocks: separate with `(* --- purpose --- *)`
- FB header: `//` comment before FUNCTION_BLOCK
